      "span_text": "Previous studies have suggested the presence of MSCs in the skin of patients with psoriasis; however, although the dermis and epidermis are known to be involved in the pathology of this disease [CITATION_1] , no study has analyzed the presence of these cells in both skin layers or the biological differences between MSCs derived from lesional versus nonlesional areas."
